Topic: Strings in Python (Complete Basics)


1Ô∏è‚É£ What is a String?

A string is a sequence of characters.

name = "Akshay"
city = 'Delhi'


Strings can be in single or double quotes.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Access Characters (Indexing)

Index starts from 0.

s = "Python"
print(s[0])   # P
print(s[3])   # h


Negative indexing:

print(s[-1])  # n

3Ô∏è‚É£ String Slicing

Used to get part of string.

s = "Python"
print(s[0:4])   # Pyth
print(s[2:])    # thon
print(s[:3])    # Pyt

4Ô∏è‚É£ String Length
s = "Python"
print(len(s))

5Ô∏è‚É£ Common String Methods (VERY IMPORTANT)
s = "python programming"

print(s.upper())      # PYTHON PROGRAMMING
print(s.lower())      # python programming
print(s.title())      # Python Programming
print(s.capitalize()) # Python programming

Check & Replace
print(s.find("python"))     # 0
print(s.replace("python", "java"))

Split & Join
s = "Python is easy"
words = s.split()
print(words)

6Ô∏è‚É£ String Comparison
a = "madam"
print(a == a[::-1])


üëâ Used for palindrome checking.

üß† Memory Trick

Index ‚Üí position

Slice ‚Üí part

Methods ‚Üí modify string

